<HEADLINE> Lions Beats Rams at Home again in Chinese Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Lions held off a
strong comeback to win their second home victory in a row over the
Guangzhou Rams 110-108 on Friday, but still three games behind of
Guangzhou in the Chinese Men's Professional basketball league.
</P>
<P>
The Rams trailed 81-94 in the third period but made a 13-6 run
to close the gap to only one point behind, 108-109, after Zhang
Hongxin's three-pointers with two minutes left.
</P>
<P>
Yuan Zhinan shot a bad basket at the lane and missed the
Rams'chance to overtake the home team in the final minute.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Degui, 38, shot a free throw off the bench to ice the
game, which made Beijing 13-9 for third place on the team
standings.
</P>
<P>
American Tyrone Doleman scored 34 points and Tang Zhijun added
27 points for Beijing. While American Guard Darren McClinton led
the Rams, who was second placed behind of the Jilin Tigers, which
recorded a 18-4 after a 107-103 win over the Tianjin Breakers
Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, the Shanghai Nanyang lost to the
Henan Wildcats 59-65 after a fighting between both players in the
second half; the Hubei Cranes defeated the Fujian Storm 131-120.
</P>
</TEXT>
