<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Inflation Rises Slightly Last December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's inflation
rose slightly to about 16.4 percent in December, 1996 compared with
13.9 percent last November, according to figures obtained from
the Reserve Bank of Zimbabwe today.
</P>
<P>
The major contributor to the rise in inflatgion in December
last year was the increase in fuel prices, salaries and wages, as
well as medical fees.
</P>
<P>
In the draft document detailing the second stage of market reforms
to be launched this year, the Zimbabwe government has pledged to
pursue fiscal and monetary policies that will reduce inflation
further to single digit figures by the year 2001. enditem

