<HEADLINE> Finland, Sweden Combat Unemployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 17 (Xinhua)-- The governments of Finland and
Sweden have launched massive crackdown on unemployment, press
reports said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to a report released by the Finnish Ministry of
Labor, 19 percent of the workforce in Finland were unemployed in
December last year, up from 17.4 percent in the previous month.
This brought to 468,000 the number of jobless people in the
country.
</P>
<P>
In Sweden, 600,000 people, or approximately 13.4 percent, were
out of job. During the first two weeks this year, 2,746 Swedes
knew they would lose their jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
