<HEADLINE> W. African Businessmen to Attend Exhibition in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Business executives from west
African countries are to attend the National Association of Home
Builders' Show in Houston, the United States, between January 24
and 27.
</P>
<P>
The visit, organized by the Abidjan Office of the U.S.
Department of Commerce and Foreign Commercial Service, is aimed
at promoting trade and investment between American builders and the
growing construction sector in west and central Africa, the News
Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will be composed of more than 70 business
executives from Nigeria, Benin, Burkina Faso, Cameroun, Cape
Verde, Chad, Cote d'Ivoire, Ghana, Guinea, Mali, Mauritania,
Senegal, Sierra Leone and Togo, the agency said, quoting a
statement issued by the U.S. Information Service in Lagos.
</P>
<P>
"The event not only brings west Africans to America, but it
encourages regional cooperation among Africans. Business people
from both Anglophone and Francophone countries can discuss
opportunities together. It is a synergetic operation," the
statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
