<HEADLINE> Delta Rocket Explodes Seconds After Liftoff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- An unmanned Delta rocket
carrying an advanced navigation satellite for the U.S. Air Force
exploded at noon today, 13 seconds after liftoff.
</P>
<P>
The rocket, lifted off at 11:28 a.m. EST (1628 GMT), is made by
McDonnell Douglas Corporation. It has been more than 10 years
since a Delta rocket blew up last time.
</P>
<P>
The advanced Global Positioning System (GPS) satellite is built
by Lockheed Martin Corporation. It had an expected lifetime of 10
years and was the 39th GPS satellite to be launched. 
</P>
