<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Praises China's Publicity, Ideological Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The overall international and
domestic situation is good at present, and so is the work in
China's publicity and ideological work, Communist Party of China
(CPC) General Secretary Jiang Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also the Chinese president, made the remark this
morning while addressing publicity department heads attending a
national conference on publicity and ideological work.
</P>
<P>
Departments in publicity and the ideological sector worked
together to build the material progress on one hand and strive for
social ethical and cultural progress on the other; they scored new
progress in various work last year following the remarkable
achievements made over the past three years since the 14th
National Party Congress, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, the Party Central Committee is satisfied
with the extensive work that has been done, mainly centered on the
convocation of the Sixth Plenary Session of the 14th Party Central
Committee, and new situation that emerged in the drive to promote
socialist ethics and cultural development.
</P>
<P>
"1997 is an important year in the history of development of our
party and country," he noted, and the publicity and ideological
sector should uphold the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics. It should also
focus on two major issues that concern the overall situation,
namely, resuming the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and
the convening of the Party's 15th National Congress. All work
should be carried in a practical and down-to-earth manner.
</P>
<P>
In a final analysis, Jiang said, if a country wants to be
stronger and develop further, its economy must be boosted.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he expressed the hope that officials in the publicity
and ideological field across the country should, in keeping with
the Party's general guidelines and arrangements for the current
conference, continue to focus on economic development and open up
a new situation as they strive for ethical and cultural progress, so
as to provide a still more powerful ideological guarantee for
advancing reform, opening-up and the modernization drive, and create
a stable and unified environment for Hong Kong's return and the
Party's 15th Congress.
</P>
<P>
Jiang concluded by wishing people in publicity and ideological
field still greater successes in their work this year,
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, a member of both the Political Bureau and the
Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee, and head of the
Propaganda Department of the CPC Central Committee, participated
in today's meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
