<HEADLINE> Sweden to Assist Tanzania in Natural resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania and Sweden
today signed an agreement under which the latter will provide
about 22 million U.S. Dollars to support Tanzania's natural
resources management in the next four years.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact signed here by Deputy Principal Secretary in
the Ministry of Finance Gray Mmgonja and Swedish Ambassador to
Tanzania Thomas Palme, the assistance will focus on sustainable
use of natural resources leading to increased production at
village level.
</P>
<P>
A press statement issued by the Swedish Embassy here today
said four districts -- Babati, Kiteto, Simanjaro and Singida
Rural areas -- would be benefited from the assistance.
</P>
<P>
It said the four districts have already worked out the program
in conjunction with the villages ready for implementation.
</P>
<P>
It further said the Prime Minister's Office would be
responsible for the coordination of this program, whose objective
include educating and counseling the people on the better use of
the natural resources.
</P>
<P>
To cap it all, the project's objective is to increase the
sustainable production of agricultural and forest products and
achieve financially sustainable development in the districts.
</P>
