<HEADLINE> France Not Against South Africa-Syria Arms Deal, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- France today said it is not
against an arms deal between South Africa and Syria despite the
United States' opposition to it, the Syrian Arab News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the news agency in Paris, French Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Eve Dotrau said Syria and South Africa are
sovereign countries and "We are for the sovereignty of
countries. That is a very important principle in the international
law."
</P>
<P>
The French official was commenting on the fact that the
U.S. pressurizes South Africa to cancel its
641-million-U.S.-dollar arms deal to sell tank-firing control
system to Syria.
</P>
<P>
Washington, which blacklisted Syria as a sponsor of
international terrorism, has reportedly threatened to stop its
118-million-dollar-aids to South Africa if it goes ahead with the
deal.
</P>
<P>
Syria, in response, has said "the U.S. stand towards the arms
deal is a flagrant interference in the internal affairs of both
Syria and South Africa, and a dictation of the U.S. law on world
countries." 
</P>
</TEXT>
