<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Becomes Key Investors in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Overseas Chinese have become
one of the key sources of foreign investment for Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Their enterprises in the Chinese capital have reached 70
percent of the total overseas-funded companies in the city.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has seen a sustained growth of foreign investment over
the past few years, standing at 33.2 billion US dollars in
contractual value last year.
</P>
<P>
"About 70 percent of overseas-backed enterprises are held in
the hands of overseas Chinese in this city," said Xu Yongsheng,
director of the Municipal Overseas Chinese Affairs Office.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese official revealed this today at pre-Spring Festival
reception for overseas Chinese entrepreneurs and their families.
</P>
<P>
He Luli, vice-chairwoman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, and Lin Wenyi,
deputy mayor of Beijing, attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
Lin encouraged the overseas Chinese community to make more
contributions to the city's economic development.  
</P>
