<HEADLINE> Pakistani President Expresses Grief over Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari expressed grief and sorrow over the tragic bomb blast in
Lahore today which killed at least 12 people.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with leaders of Punjab province, Leghari also
expressed condolence for families of the victims in the blast that
occurred earlier this afternoon in the Punjab capital city.
</P>
<P>
Punjab Governor Khawaja Ahmad Tariq Rahim and caretaker Chief
Minister Mian Afzal Hayat cut short the meeting with the president
and rushed back to Lahore immediately.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders asked the local administration to extend
maximum assistance and best possible medical treatment for the
injured.
</P>
<P>
They urged the administration to provide financial assistance
for the family of those who lost their lives in the blast.
</P>
<P>
They also asked the departments concerned to look into the
causes of the explosion as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chief Minister of North West Frontier Province Raja
Sikandar Zaman Khan expressed his grief and sorrow over the tragic
incident and condemned the cowardly act of terrorism.  
</P>
