<HEADLINE> Italians Win World Cup Two-man Bobsled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Italian Guenther Huber and his
teammate defeated their rivals to win the two-man World Cup
bobsled race in Koenigssee, Germany on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Huber and Antonio Tartaglia, the Olympic bronze medalists,
clocked a two-heat total time of one minute, 36.45 seconds, 0.01
seconds faster than Germany's Dostthaler and Thomas Platzer in a
race that doubled as European championship.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Reto Goetschi and Guido Acklin finished in a
third-place tie with USA II, with driver Brian Shimer and Robert
Olesen. Both teams were timed in 1:37.08.
</P>
<P>
Huber and Tartaglia lead the World Cup standings with 164
points after five of seven races. The second place went to
Canada's Pierre Lueders and Matt Hindle with 152, followed by
Dosttahler's team, 140. 
</P>
</TEXT>
