<HEADLINE> Weihai to Improve Quality of Industrial Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Measures are planned to improve
the industrial quality in Weihai in east China's Shandong
Province. The coastal city has emerged as one of the country's
richest areas since the policy of reform and opening-up was
initiated in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Weihai will take measures such as optimizing its capital
structure, improving management and upgrading technologies, all
targeted as the city's three major tasks this year.
</P>
<P>
According to a blueprint, the city is to require 280 local
enterprises to obtain internationally--recognised GBI9000 and
ISO9000 standard certificates this year.
</P>
<P>
Weihai will set aside 4.2 billion yuan this year, up 15 percent
from 1996, to boost technical renovation work.
</P>
<P>
City government officials said that electronic technologies
will play an even more important role in transforming traditional
industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
