<HEADLINE> Poland's Malysz Wins World Cup Ski Jumping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Polish teenager Adam Malysz
claimed his second World Cup victory in a normal hill competition
in Sapporo, Japan, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Malysz, 19, leapt 93 meters in his second try to clinch victory
with a total of 239 points. His first jump of 89.5 had left him
down in sixth place on Sapporo's Miyanomori jumping hill.
</P>
<P>
His only previous World Cup victory was in the final event of
the 1996 series in Oslo last March.
</P>
<P>
Mika Laitinen of Finland posted the longest jump of 94 meters
in the second round to share second place with Norway's Sturle
Holseter, who recorded 92.5 and 90 for 234 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
