<HEADLINE> Taliban Moving to Panjshir Valley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan ruling Taliban
militia moved northward today to the opposition's stronghold of
the Panjshir Valley, said reports from the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
After capturing most of Kapisa Province last week, the Taliban
came close to the town of Gulbahar, 100 kilometers north of Kabul,
near the mouth of the Panjshir Valley.
</P>
<P>
Because of its strategic location, Gulbahar is said to be the
key to entering the Panjshir, stronghold of ex-Defense Minister
Ahmad Shah Masood who fled there when the Taliban took the capital
of Kabul last September.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, the Taliban took the strategic Bagram Airbase,
50 kilometers north of Kabul, and the nearby town of Charikar,
capital Parwan Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
