<HEADLINE> International Lion Dance Tournament Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen troupes from 10
countries and regions are vying for the championship in the Hong
Kong International Lion Dance Invitation Tournament, which was
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Pao Ping-wing, chairman of the Organizing Committee, said: "The
 event is an excellent opportunity for international lion dance
troupes to exchange skills and promote the sport of Chinese
heritage."
</P>
<P>
The two-day tournament has attracted competing teams from
Belgium, Brunei, Canada, China, Taiwan, Macao, Hong Kong,
Singapore, Thailand and the United States.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a spectacular contest of the southern Chinese lion
dance," said Pao. Originated from southern China's Guangdong
Province, the lion dance features colorful costumes and bold
appearance. Spectators can enjoy the contestants' superb skills in
 presenting the joy, anger, sorrow, delight and physical strength
and movement of a lion.
</P>
<P>
Each troupe will be required to perform a 10- to 12-minute
dance.
</P>
<P>
The tournament is organized by the Urban Council and the Hong
Kong Chinese Martial Arts Association. The final will be held
tomorrow evening at the Hong Kong Coliseum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
