<HEADLINE> 21 Policemen, 2 Home Guards Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- At least 21 policemen and two
home guards were killed and 16 policemen and two home guards
injured when they confronted Tamil rebels in North-Central
Province of Sri Lanka today, a military spokesman said this
evening.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said a group of Tamil rebels attacked the police
post at Kanugahawewa in Anuradhapura District this morning.
</P>
<P>
Reinforcements were rushed to the location and fought back the
rebels, he said.
</P>
<P>
The casualties were evacuated to Anuradhapura Hospital, the
spokesman, adding that Tamil rebels casualties were not yet known.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year-old war for an
independent homeland for minority Tamils in the north and east of
the country.  
