<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Premier Expects Reform to Enhance Power Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese premier Li Peng has
expressed hope that the establishment of a State Power Corporation
will help promote a better and faster development of the nation's
power industry.
</P>
<P>
Setting up the new corporation, which is part of the reform of
government structures, is aimed at enabling the power
administration system to keep in line with market rules, Li said
at a meeting on reform of the industry.
</P>
<P>
The State Power Corporation, which was officially inaugurated
two days ago, is a state-owned business entitled to manage the
nation-wide power network and inter-regional power
transmission. Its establishment is expected to lead to the
abolition of the current Ministry of Power Industry after a period
of operation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese president Jiang Zemin wrote an inscription to
congratulate the new corporation on its inauguration, calling on
the industry to make new contributions to the development of the
national economy and social progress.
</P>
<P>
After hearing reports from Shi Dazhen, general manager of the
corporation, and other industry officials at Friday's meeting, Li
said that by taking the reform measures, China wants to diversify
sources of investment in power generation facilities and
facilitate the industry's development.
</P>
<P>
He urged the corporation to play a leading role in the national
economy and serve the public well.
</P>
<P>
The premier asked all enterprises within the power industry to
enhance technological progress and strengthen management to help
cut costs and increase efficiency.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that in the coming years, more government
departments administrating industrial affairs will gradually
convert to corporations or industrial associations so that
governmental and business functions can be separated in accordance
with market rules.
</P>
<P>
Vice premier Wu Bangguo presided over yesterday's meeting. He
delivered a speech at the opening ceremony of the corporation two
days earlier, hailing the reform measures of the power industry as
an important structural readjustment.
</P>
<P>
Wu asked the Ministry of Power Industry to separate its
functions as a power management business. He called for the State
Power Corporation to achieve normal operations as soon as
possible.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
