<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rebels Kill 200 People, Abduct 300 in Northern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Lord's
Resistance Army (LRA) killed at least 200 people in northern
Uganda last week and abducted another 300 to Sudan for military
training, reports reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
Reports from local councillors of Kitgum District registered
at least 175 names of victims of slaughter in Lokung sub-county,
43 in Palabek-gem sub-county, seven in Madi Opei subcounty and
36 in Padibe County.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Gulu District said LRA rebels killed 26
civilians. Louis Otika, Resident District Commissioner of Gulu,
confirmed the atrocity but added that the number of the victims
is still to be checked.
</P>
<P>
Public Relation Officer of the government troops in the north
Shaban Bantariza told "the New Vision" that LRA rebels resorted
to massacre because they failed to capture towns from the Ugandan
army.
</P>
<P>
Resident District Commissioner in Kitgum George Willy Odwong
told local officials and members of parliament that LRA rebels
had abducted 300 civilians to Sudan for forced military training.
</P>
<P>
In Kitgum alone, some 2,000 civilians have fled their home in the
wake of the atrocities, the local media estimated.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
