<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Installs Optical Cables of 2,200 km </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
laid 2,204 kilometers of optical cables in 1996, forming a
province-wide advanced telecom system based on three loop optical
transmission networks.
</P>
<P>
The three loop networks, which were finished last year, are
located in the north, south and central parts of the province, and
link the province to national-level optical trunks, such as
Beijing-Wuhan-Guangzhou, Beijing-Shenyang-Harbin,
Beijing-Hohhot-Yinchuan-Lanzhou, and Beijing-Jiujiang-Guangzhou
Cable lines, said the journal "Communication Weekly."
</P>
<P>
This year, the province will speed up work on a project for a
800-km optical cable section, which will supplement a telecom
artery connecting four provincial capital cities, including
Shijiazhuang, Jinan and Taiyuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the construction of 3,000 km of local optical cables
and telephone networks is also under way. When completed, Hebei's
optical telecom density rate will be significantly improved, and
an optical web will cover every corner of the province, the
journal said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
