<HEADLINE> India's Population to Cross 1 Billion Mark Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- India's population will cross
the 1 billion mark by the turn of the century, Registrar General
Dr. M. Vijayanunni said here today.
</P>
<P>
The total fertility rate will be around 3 percent at the
beginning of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The country's urban population is expected to rise to 291
million by the year 2001, compared with about 218 million in 1991,
he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
