<HEADLINE> Sampras Romps into Last 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete Sampras
of the UNited States demolished doubles specialist Mark Woodforde
6-1, 6-0, 6-1 to cruise into the last 16 of the Australian Open in
Melbourne on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras produced textbook serves and fierce forehands to wrap
up the match in one hour and 19 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The 28th ranked Woodforde, a 31-year-old who has won almost
every honour in the game in men's doubles, was a surprise
semi-finalist in Melbourne last year.
</P>
<P>
Sampras's next opponent will be the unseeded Dominik
Hrbaty of Slovakia. 
</P>
