<HEADLINE> Extradited KLF Leader Taken into Custody </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Indian police today arrested
self-styled Khalistan Liberation Front ( KLF) leader A.S. Lahoria
and his wife and put them into custody as soon as they arrived
here from the US, which extradited them.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Indian Central Bureau of Investigation and police
authority had sent a five-member team to the US for their
extradition.
</P>
<P>
Lahoria has been involved in a number of murder cases including
the killing of Congress leader Lalit Maken and former army chief
gen. A.S. Vaidya. He was also involved in the assassination
attempt on the former Indian Youth Congress chief M. Singh Bitta
in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Lahoria was arrested in the US last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
