<HEADLINE> One Suspect in Bomb Blast Arrested in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 18 (Xinhua) -- One suspect in a bomb blast
that killed at least 12 persons in Pakistan's eastern city of
Lahore this afternoon was arrested on the spot, the official
Associated Press of Pakistan reported.
</P>
<P>
The city police chief, Tariq Saleem Dogar, was quoted as saying
that the suspect fled from the blast scene at the District and
Sessions Court of Lahore immediately after the explosion and was
caught before he could make it to the entrance.
</P>
<P>
The suspect has been handed over to local authorities for
further interrogation. Preliminary interrogation showed that the
suspect has some link with the blast.
</P>
<P>
At least 12 people were killed and about 30 others injured in
the blast in Punjab's provincial capital. A leader of a religious
militant group and two local journalists were among the dead.
</P>
<P>
Last year, about 80 people were killed in various bomb
incidents in Punjab province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
