<HEADLINE> Fire Breaks Out at Gas Cylinder Depot in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Fire broke out this morning at a
gas cylinder storehouse in al-Moatamadia, Imbaba, west of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
A security source said that the fire has led to the explosion of
a number of gas cylinders, the Egyptian MENA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters have managed to control the fire and protect
houses nearby from being caught in the flames.
</P>
<P>
The firemen are still braving the fire by freezing the
cylinders so as to prevent any more explosions.
</P>
