<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Religious Leader Killed in Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 18 (Xinhua) -- One religious leader was
among the 12 killed in a bomb blast in the eastern Pakistan city
of Lahore early this afternoon, said local reports.
</P>
<P>
Maulana Ziaur Rahman of Sapah-e-Sahaba Pakistan (SSP) was
killed and Maulana Azam Tariq Rahim, another SSP leader, was
critically injured in the blast while 30 other people were also
wounded.
</P>
<P>
Two local journalists were among the dead in the incident while
two judges were injured.
</P>
<P>
When the bomb went off at the District and Sessions Court of
Lahore, capital of Punjab Province, the two SSP leaders, who were
earlier arrested in connection with various cases of sectarian
violence, were produced before the court for grant of bail.
</P>
<P>
A large number of litigants who suffered injures in the
explosion are being removed to local hospitals for medical
treatment.
</P>
<P>
According to bomb disposal sources, the high-intensity bomb,
rocking the building of the court during peak hours this
afternoon, was believed to have been planted in a motorcycle in
the court where a large number of people were present and have
been remote-controlled.  
</P>
</TEXT>
