<HEADLINE> Bahrain to Host Arab Property Rights Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain will host the second
Arab International Conference on Protection of Intellectual Rights
in the Arab countries, which will be held on April 21-22,
according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The conference, organized by the Arab Society for the
Protection of Industrial Property, will be held in the Bahraini
capital of Manama to deal with ways that can help owners of
intellectual property protect their rights, products and profits,
Bahrain's Prime Minister Sheikh khalifa bin Sulman al-Khalifa said
in his message to the organizers.
</P>
<P>
Participants will also discuss the methods companies can use to
ensure protection against piracy, and relevant international
treaties and licensing arrangement regulating intellectual
property rights, according to the message. 
</P>
