<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Eastern Jayapura, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.3 on
the Richter scale shocked the eastern town of Jayapura in
Indonesia's Irian Jaya province this morning.
</P>
<P>
The source of the tremor was at a depth of 25 kilometers at
2.72 south latitude and 140.82 east longitude, Antara news agency
quoted Putu Pudja, head of the local office of meteorology and
geophysics, as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The tremor was quite strong but claimed no victims," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said a series of tremors occurred during the week but they
were too small to be recorded by the office equipment.  
</P>
