<HEADLINE> Injured French Skier Comes out of Coma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- French skier Adrien Duvillard,
who lost consciousness after a training crash for a World Cup
downhill on Friday, was reportedly out of his coma overnight and
in a stable condition.
</P>
<P>
Doctors upgraded his condition from serious to stable on
Saturday and reported he had full movement of both his arms and
legs.
</P>
<P>
Duvillard, who also suffered broken ribs and a punctured
lung in the accident, will remain in hospital for seven to 10
days for observation and tests.
</P>
<P>
The crash occured when he lost control on the final turn of the
Lauberhorn course and crashed at the same spot where Austrian
Gernot Reinstadler was killed six years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
