<HEADLINE> Top Seed Audina Advances to Women's Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Olympic silver medalist Mia
Audina of Indonesia overwhelmed world champion Ye Zhaoying of
China 12-9, 11-6, entering the women's singles final at the
Yonex Japan Open Badminton Tournament here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In the other hard-fought semi-finals match, second seed China's
Gong Zhichao defeated last week's Chinese Taipei Open champion
Camilla Martin of Denmark 12-11, 6-11, 11-2.
</P>
<P>
In the men's semi-finals, unseeded Peter Rasmussen of Denmark
ousted Ardi Wiranata of Indonesia 15-2, 15-5 while ninth-seeded
Park Sung-woo of South Korea came from behind to win from Chinese
Taipei Open champion Peter Gade Christensen of Denmark 13-18,
15-10, 15-5.
</P>
<P>
Audina, the world's top-ranked player, climbed to the No. 1
singles rank after winning the U.S. Open singles title last
September.
</P>
<P>
19-year-old Gong, winner of the 1996 Asian Championships, edged
Audina in their only match so far, at the World Grand Prix Finals
in Jakarta in November.
</P>
<P>
The 170,000 U.S. dollars Japan Open badminton is the second in
the 20 badminton Grand Prix Circuit series this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
