Kuan Yew, Deputy Prime Minister Lee Hsien Loong, Deputy Prime
Minister and Defense Minister Tony Tan, Minister for Law and
Minister for Foreign Affairs S. Jayakumar, Finance Minister
Richard Hu and Home Affairs Minister Wong Kan Seng.
</P>
<P>
Those who retained their positions in the new cabinet also
include Labor Minister Lee Boon Yang, Minister for Communications
Mah Bow Tan, Minister Without Portfolio Lim Boon Heng, Minister
for National Development Lim Hng Kiang and Minister for Community
Development Abdullah Tarmugi.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet will be sworn in by President Ong Teng Cheong
next Saturday.  
