<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Myanmar Issue Joint Communique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Myanmar are satisfied
with positive development of the friendship and multi-faceted
cooperation between the two countries over the past two years,
said a a press communique published here today.
</P>
<P>
The press communique was jointly issued by the two countries
after the second meeting of the Vietnam-Myanmar joint commission
which was held here on January 15-18.
</P>
<P>
The two delegations were respectively headed by Vietnamese
Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam and Mynamar Foreign Minister U
Ohn Gyaw.
</P>
<P>
They also expressed their pleasure at the growing exchanges of
visits by Vietnamese and Mynamar high-ranking officials and at the
positive growth of trade as well as the development of cultural,
social and economic cooperation between the two nations since the
first meeting of the joint commission was held in Vietnam in March
1995, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
At this second meeting, the commission reviewed the cooperation
between the two countries in general and the implementation of the
agreement signed at the first meeting in particular, and pointed
out measures to further boost their multi-faceted cooperative
ties, especially that in trade, agriculture and forestry.
</P>
<P>
According to the press communique, the next meeting of the
commission will be held in Mynamar. 
</P>
