<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Singapore Cabinet Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong
unveiled the lineup of his new cabinet today with most of the
members of the last cabinet retaining their positions.
</P>
<P>
One major change in the new cabinet is that former Education
Minister Lee Yock Suan has been appointed minister of trade and
industry and second minister of finance, while former Trade and
Industry Minister Yew Cheow Tong has been designated minister of
health and minister of the environment.
</P>
<P>
Teo Chee Hean is now the minister of education and second
minister of defense, while George Yeo is still the minister of
information and the arts. He is also second minister of trade and
industry.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released today, the prime minister's office said
the prime minister and his cabinet colleagues will be sworn in by
President Ong Teng Cheong at 12:00 noon next Saturday at the City
Hall Chamber.
</P>
<P>
It said Deputy Prime Minister Tony Tan, who is also minister of
defense, will take charge of the two universities of Singapore on
behalf of the minister of education, Teo Chee Hean, for the period
when Teo is second minister of defense.
</P>
<P>
There will be a second cabinet change within two years, in
order to enable the minister of communications and the minister of
national development to remain in their present ministries to see
through and ensure the smooth implementation of certain major
programs, the office said.  
</P>
