<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unseeded Belgian Stuns World Second Seed in Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Belgian Dominique Van
Roost ousted second seed Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain from the
Australian Open tennis tournament Saturday morning in Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
The 43rd-ranked Van Roost overcame an injury to her arm late in
the match to beat the two-time Open finalist and world number
three by 1-6, 6-4 and 8-6.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Van Roost, formerly Dominique Monami, won the
Tasmanian International in the lead up to the Open, reached fourth
round of the grand slam for the second time in her career.
</P>
<P>
She also made the last 16 at the Open in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario, winner of the French Open and the US Open in
1994 and two-time runner-up in 1994 and 1995 in Melbourne, failed
to display her form as brightly as in seasons past. 
</P>
</TEXT>
