<HEADLINE> 8 Policemen Killed, Over 20 Injured In Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Eight policemen were killed and
more than 20 others injured during fighting with Tamil rebels in
North-Central Province of Sri Lanka today, according to informed
sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that a group of Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) rebels attacked a police station in Anuradpura
District this morning.
</P>
<P>
No further details were available, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north and east of the island country.
</P>
</TEXT>
