<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Surin Wins 60 Meters at Montreal Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Bruny Surin finished first in a
60-meter sprint at the Montreal Athletics Grand Prix on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian, two-time world indoor champion, clocked his
winning time of 6.60 seconds, beating teammate Robert Esmie by a
stride.
</P>
<P>
American Vince Henderson finished third in 6.68.
</P>
<P>
"For me, this is a chance to race in Canada, especially here in
Montreal where I live, it was important to win," said Surin.
</P>
<P>
In other events, D'Andre Hill of the United States won the
women's 60 metres in 7.43 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Kwaku Boateng, a Ghana native living in Montreal, won the high
jump at 2.27 metres. 
</P>
</TEXT>
