<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Help Probe in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Truth and
Reconciliation Commission (TRC) of South Africa is to assist the
Rwandan government to investigate into the 1994 genocide in that
country, the local daily The Citizen reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The TRC, an independent organization authorized by the
government to investigate human rights violations during the
apartheid era, is to meet a six-member Rwandan government
delegation next Saturday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the two countries will explore ways of
promoting bilateral cooperation and mutual understanding, TRC
Deputy Chairman Alex Boraine was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan visit to South Africa follows a week-long visit by TRC
officials to Rwanda in September last year.
</P>
<P>
About 500,000 people were killed in the genocide Rwanda in
1994. enditem

