<HEADLINE> Tanzania Receives Japanese Financial Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Japan has granted
Tanzania 5.4 billion Tanzania Shillings (about nine million U.S.
Dollars) for improvement of bridges on trunk roads and polio
eradication projects in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to a local newspaper today, the agreement was signed
here Friday by Japanese Ambassador Shintaro Sasaki and Acting
Minister for Finance of Tanzania Daniel Yone.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, 3.3 billion T.Shs (about 5.5 million
Dollars) of the money will be used for materials
and services for the improvement of four bridges on the
Mtwara-Minngoyo road.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 2.1 billion T.Shs (about 3.5 million Dollars)
will go to the purchase of polio vaccine and equipment to
enhance immunization activities in the country. 
</P>
