<HEADLINE> American Balloonist Gains Permission from Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- American adventurer Steve
Fossett obtained a last-minute permission to overfly Libya's air
space late Friday, continuing his bid to become the first man for
the non-stop round-the-world balloon flight.
</P>
<P>
Early, Fossett had to make a detour as Libya denied his request
to fly over its territory, and the delay may add one day to his
trip, said spokesman Alan Blount.
</P>
<P>
This was the second time when Fossett in his "Solo Spirit" has
encountered the issue of the kind.
</P>
<P>
Fossett was forced to change his itinery on Tuesday when he was
traveling toward Scandinavia to avoid flying over Russia that
denied his flight in its airspace.
</P>
<P>
Two other teams of balloonists had failed in recent attempts to
fly around the world starting from Morocco and Switzerland.
</P>
