<HEADLINE> Cell, Genetic Engineering Lab Set up in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Cell and Genetic
Engineering Laboratory of Zhejiang, the first bio-engineering lab
in the east Chinese province, has passed appraisal by a team of
experts.
</P>
<P>
The lab, an advanced level installation in China, was launched
last September as part of a provincial hi-tech industrial
development strategy.
</P>
<P>
It is based on the School of Life Sciences of Hangzhou
University, and involved an investment of 1.5 million yuan for the
first phase of the development.
</P>
<P>
The lab consists of experimental centers in genetic
engineering, cell engineering, pharmaceutical and biological
engineering, and animals and plants.
</P>
<P>
So far, it has undertaken 21 research topics, trained 200
professional personnel and cooperated with research organs in the
United States, Germany, Japan and Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
