<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sanchez Vicario Bows Out of Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Arantxa Sanchez
Vicario crashed out of the Australian Open in the third round on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The world number three woman player was beaten by Belgian
Dominique van Roost 1-6, 6-4 and 8-6, recording her worst
performance in a grand slam for five years.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario, losing finalist in five of the last eight
grand slam events, won the first set in a hurry but fell away
badly in the following two sets to concede her defeat.
</P>
<P>
Van Roost, ranked 43 in the world, survived an injury to her
right elbow to seal the competition in two hours and 14 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario lost the final twice at Melbourne Park in 1994
and 1995 and Van Roost has never progressed beyond the fourth
round at a grand slam event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
