<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Muster Enters Last 16 of Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Fifth seed Thomas Muster won a
tiebreaker to enter the last 16 of the Australian Open tennis
tournament with straight sets victory in Melbourne on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian, a clay court specialist, saved a dozen of break
points against German qualifier Jens Knippschild before winning
6-4, 7-6 (7-2), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Muster, 1995 French Open champion, survived a string of scares
and repeatedly clawed his way back from two or three break points
down to hold serve.
</P>
<P>
With two sets in hand, Muster then rushed to a 5-0 lead in the
third set.
</P>
<P>
The clay-court specialist will meet eighth seeded South African
Wayne Ferreira or unseeded Italian Renzo Furlan in the next round.
</P>
</TEXT>
