<HEADLINE> Singapore to Open Factory in Yangon IndustriaL Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's Myanmar Megasteel
Industries Ltd. will set up a galvanized iron sheet factory in the
Yangon Hlaingthaya Industrial Zone with an investment of 9.13
million U.S. dollars and 1.8 million kyats in the local currency,
the official paper the New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
This will become the second foreign-invested factory to be
established in the industrial zone just after a dairy products
factory was set up there by a joint British-French company last
week.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, a land-lease contract for the factory
between the Human Settlement and Housing Development Department of
the Myanmar government and the Singapore company was signed here
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, the Singapore company will lease a
2.4-hectare plot in the zone for an initial 30-year period, with
two extra five-year extension periods.
</P>
<P>
The factory will produce 3,000 tons of galvanized iron sheets
annually for local sales and for export.  
</P>
</TEXT>
