<HEADLINE> Ex-Im Bank Finances Qatar Developments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The United States
Export-Import Bank today announced it had approved a financing
project providing 526 million U.S. dollars to support American
sales for two gas field development projects.
</P>
<P>
The export of U.S. equipment and services for the Ras Laffan
and Qatargas Projects, sponsored by subsidiaries of Mobil Corp.,
will sustain thousands of American jobs. The projects will tap the
world's largest gas field, the North Field located offshore Qatar.
</P>
<P>
The Bank will offer 464 million dollars to finance U.S. exports
to Ras Laffan Liquefied Natural Gas Co. Ltd, to build, own and
operate offshore and onshore facilities at the North Field.
</P>
<P>
The deal also includes up to 62 million dollars in financing
the sale of U.S. equipment and services for the upstream part of
the Qatargas Liquefied Natural Gas Project.
</P>
<P>
The financers of the two projects will be repaid from projects'
revenues, rather than relying on a guarantee of the debt by the
host country government.
</P>
<P>
The Bank is a government agency that provides guarantees for,
and finances U.S. exports abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
