<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Rebel Intelligence Operatives Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 18 (Xinhua)-- Sri Lankan police have arrested
six Tamil rebel intelligence operatives who were in Colombo to
gather information about the movements of VIPs and conduct
surveillance of key army and police installations.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources today, there are still 50 such
operatives in Colombo city.
</P>
<P>
The six arrested rebels had confessed that they had been given
six months to complete their reconnaissance missions and report
back to their bosses so that steps could be taken to cause carnage
in Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
One of the operatives was arrested at a Colombo lodge recently,
leading to the arrest of the other five, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Further inquiries are being conducted by the Colombo police.
</P>
</TEXT>
