<HEADLINE> Nepali Official Accused of Violating Adoption Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of Nepal's
Home Ministry is facing corruption charges after he permitted a
foreign couple to adopt two children in Nepal, the local press
said today.
</P>
<P>
The Commission for the Investigation of Abuse of Authority
(CIAA), the country's corruption control body, has decided to file
a lawsuit soon against Home Secretary Padmaraj Pokhrel on charges
of violating the adoption law, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The CIAA is collecting necessary documents and will file the
case at the Appellate Court, probably within a week.
</P>
<P>
According to CIAA sources, Pokhrel earlier permitted a Spanish
couple to adopt two children from an orphanage in eastern Nepal
although the adoption law prohibits one foreigner from adopting
more than one child in the country.
</P>
<P>
They claimed that Pokhrel had permitted the double adoption in
spite of the suggestion by the Ministry of Law that it would be
illegal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
