<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Talks With Mauritanian Parliament Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NOUAKCHOTT, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice
Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen held talks today with the
President of Mauritanian National Assembly, Cheikh Sid Ahmed Ould
Sidi Baba.
</P>
<P>
Both sides said they are happy with the development of
bilateral relations and agreed on further cooperation in
international issues and economic fields.
</P>
<P>
They shared the view that each country had its own
characteristics and therefore had the right to decide by and for
itself in domestic affairs. No foreign intervention should be
allowed.
</P>
<P>
They expressed hope that the two parliaments strengthen
exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During his one-day visit to the Western African country, Qian
also met with other Mauritanian leaders. They signed an
inter-governmental agreement on economic and technological
cooperation and an exchange of notes on China's donation of 1,000
tons of wheat to Mauritania.
</P>
<P>
Mauritania, which established diplomatic relations with China
in 1965, is Qian's fourth stop in his current five-nation African
tour.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who earlier visited Niger, Equatorial Guinea and Sao Tome
and Principe, flew to Cape Verde this afternoon, beginning his
visit to the small island country in the Atlantic. 
