<HEADLINE> East Chinese Province Reports Record Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The export volume of east China's
Shandong Province exceeded the 10 billion US dollar mark for the
first time in 1996.
</P>
<P>
It reported exports worth 10.6 billion US dollars last year,
putting it fourth in the country.
</P>
<P>
Customs statistics show that the province's total foreign trade
volume stood at 17.4 billion US dollars, and had a trade surplus
of 3.8 billion US dollars. Its export grew by 10 percent, 6.7
percentage points higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded ventures in the province reported 4.6 billion US
dollars worth of exports, up 32 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that provincial authorities' policies supported key
foreign trade companies last year, a move that played a positive
role in the growth of foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The majority of foreign trade companies in the province are
operating in the black, with just a few in tight financial
conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
