<HEADLINE> APMT Postpones Launch of Satellite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Asia Pacific Mobile
Telecommunications (APMT) has decided to postpone the launch of
its satellite until the end of this year pending further checks on
the new technology used on it, the local press reported.
</P>
<P>
The shareholders wanted to be sure the new technology would be
appropriate, said Rachanee Yingchairuk, president of Asia Pacific
Mobile Telecommunications (Thailand) Co., a Thai investor in the
Singapore-initiated project.
</P>
<P>
The satellite was originally scheduled for launch this month to
meet rising regional demand for mobile phones and the project
involved investors from Thailand, Singapore, Indonesia, China, the
Philippines and Vietnam, according to Rachanee.
</P>
<P>
Other mobile phone projects using the satellite would also be
postponed, Rachanee said.  
