<HEADLINE> China Develops Quasi-express Passenger Trains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Seventy China-built
quasi-express passenger trains with a speed of 160 kilometer per
hour will soon hit the country's rail tracks.
</P>
<P>
The trains, which have a maximum speed of 183 kilometers per
hour, were manufactured by the Sifang Rolling Stock Plant.
</P>
<P>
They are scheduled to run on railways under the Beijing and
Shanghai railway administrations and on the Guangzhou-Shenzhen
railway.
</P>
<P>
Experts agreed that the development of the quasi-express
passenger trains with air conditioning facilities indicates that
China's manufacturing of passenger trains has entered a new era.
</P>
