<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Masuoka Wins Stage in Dakar Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Hiroshi Masuoka of Japan drove
his Mitsubishi to win the 13th stage of the Dakar rally on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Masuoka, who had his best second place in the second stage,
beat German Jutta Kleinschmidt by 19 seconds in the tough 604-km
stage from Nema to Kiffa in Mauritania.
</P>
<P>
The top four places overall, all occupied by Mitsubishis with
Masuoka fourth, did not change while Kleinschmidt retained fifth
place.
</P>
<P>
But Japanese Kenjiro Shinozuka increased his overall lead from
23 seconds to nearly five minutes over second-placed Frenchman
Jean-Pierre Fontenay.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's penultimate stage takes the rally back into Senegal,
a 751 kms stage to Saint-Louis, with a 166-km special.
</P>
<P>
The motorcycle section also produced also saw Frenchman Eric
Bernard on a KTM to win his first Dakar rally.
</P>
<P>
Overall leader Frenchman Stephane Peterhansel, four times Dakar
winner, is more than two and a half hours ahead of second-placed
Spaniard Oscar Gallardo on a Cagiva. 
</P>
