<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austrian Chancellor Calls for European Neutrality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Chancellor Franz
Vranitzky today stressed the importance of neutrality, and the key
role of the Organization for Security and Cooperation (OSCE) in
building European security.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the parliament assembly of the OSCE,
Vranitzky said the security policy of Europe should not focus on
the eastward expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO).
</P>
<P>
It should take into consideration all other organizations
concerned such as the United Nations (U.N.), the OSCE, the
European Council (EC), the European Union (EU) and the Western
European Union (WEU).
</P>
<P>
Vranitzky said the basic principles of neutrality should be
used in building Europe's security system. They included
non-participation in other countries' wars and not resorting to
violence for national interests.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the security of Europe must be connected
with Russia. There would be no real security if Russia was
excluded, he said.
</P>
<P>
Vranitzky called for a strengthening of the OSCE's role,
pointing out that the organization was wide-ranging both in
geography and politics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
