<HEADLINE> Wiegers Wins Wins Women's 1,500 in Speed Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Ellen Wiegers beat top
favourite Marinella Canclini to win the women's 1,500 meters in
the inaugural European Short-Track Speed Skating Championships in
Malmo, Sweden on Friday.
</P>
<P>
As Canclini of Italy fell in the semifinal and failed to
qualify for the final, the 16-year-old Wiegers of the Netherlands
won an evenly-matched finale.
</P>
<P>
Wiegers stole the top honor in 2:41.571, edging over Russian
Elena Tikhanina who finished second in 2:41.819 and Evgenia
Radanova of Bulgaria third in 2:42.070.
</P>
<P>
Canclini had earlier set a fastest time of two minutes 33.345
seconds to win her preliminary heat, more than eight seconds
faster than Wiegers clocked in the final.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Mirko Vuillermin, Olympic champion at the Lillehammer
Games in 1994, won the men's 1,500 meters title in a time of
2:33.215.
</P>
<P>
Swede Martin Johansson was second in 2:33.311 and Bruno Loscos
of France third in 2:33.440. 
</P>
</TEXT>
