<HEADLINE> CIS Premiers Approve Economic Integration Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Prime Ministers of the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) approved a draft concept
of economic integration in Moscow on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference following the one-day meeting of
the premiers, Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said the
90-page document will be approved by the CIS Council of Heads of
State "possibly in late January."
</P>
<P>
He described the document as a medium-term program of
cooperation within the CIS primarily in the economic sphere.
</P>
<P>
At Friday's meeting, the premiers also discussed ways to
implement the draft concept in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Other items of the meeting's agenda included a convention on
the protection of the rights of investors, implementation of
arbitration rulings, support of small businesses, transport
tariffs, cooperation in the use of cellular communication
facilities, nuclear energy and application of the value-added
tax. 
