<HEADLINE> Xinfeng Known as Largest Cotton Village in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- It is known as the capital of
cotton, a small village where virtually every household relies on
the raw material for clothing to earn a living.
</P>
<P>
Xinfeng Village in east China's Jiangsu province, is now
renowned nationally for its large-scale cotton industry.
</P>
<P>
Known as the number one cotton village in China, Xinfeng has
been taking a lead for almost a decade among China's villages in
respect of cotton growing.
</P>
<P>
Last year 454 hectares of cotton were planted in the village,
with output reaching 700,000 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The local government attributed the achievements to help from a
village-run cotton research institute.
</P>
<P>
Four research fellows from the institute have helped local
farmers solve two major problems -- density of crops and serious
crop pests.
</P>
<P>
Advanced techniques were spread to cotton farmers through
various channels, such as on-the-spot meetings and local
broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
With their efforts, 80 percent of the thousand cotton farmer
households in the village now earn more than 10,000 yuan a year
from cotton production.
</P>
<P>
Enjoying high profits, local farmers have great enthusiasm for
cotton production. The village, for ten years running, has
maintained its cotton-planting areas of more than 400 hectares.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
