<HEADLINE> Ningbo Becomes China's Third Largest Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo Port in Zhejiang Province
now ranks third in China in terms of handling capacity.
</P>
<P>
A statistical report provided by the Ministry of Communications
shows that the port handled 76.38 million tons of cargo in 1996,
behind only Shanghai and Qinhuangdao.
</P>
<P>
Since the Ningbo port successfully shipped more than 10 million
tons of cargo in 1985, it has focused on the expansion of the
transport of iron ore, crude oil, coal, liquefied chemicals and
sundry goods.
</P>
<P>
While working jointly with Shanghai to develop into an
international shipping center, Ningbo is also in the process of
transforming its container wharf.  
