have recently attended a five-day seminar in Shanghai to discuss
the reform of small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The event, sponsored by the UN Development Program (UNDP) and
the China Hainan Academy of Reform and Development Research, was
held in the Shanghai Baoshan Steel Works, one of the largest steel
makers in the country.
</P>
<P>
The meeting discussed the development of small and medium-sized
enterprises and special economic zones in the countries of
conference participants: China, Mongolia, Vietnam, Laos, the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea, Cambodia, Myanmar,
Kazakhstan, Kyrghyzstan and Uzbekistan. The economic structures of
all these countries are confronted with a transition to market
economies.
</P>
<P>
The event has helped foster economic cooperation and exchanges
among the nations, experts said.
</P>
<P>
A similar meeting, the first of its kind, was convened in China
last March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
