<HEADLINE> Brazil's Oil Output Up in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's oil output increased
by 13 percent to 901,000 barrels a day in 1996 over the previous
year, Petrobras, the biggest state oil enterprise in Brazil,
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Petrobras attributed the rise to the high operational
efficiency reached by the company in Bacia de Campos, which
contributed 69 percent of the national production with 618,380
barrels a day, and the exploration in Rio Grande de Norte and in
Amazonia.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's oil output will have reached one million barrels a day
by the end of this year, said the source.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's oil production covers 60 percent of the domestic
demand. 
</P>
