<HEADLINE> Cigarette Smoking Decreases in Venezuela in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's cigarette market
contracted 26 percent in 1996 from 1995, National Tobacco
Co. marketing manager Jayme K. Fowler said.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, cigarette smokers contributed 21.18 million U.S.
dollars in taxes, Fowler was quoted as saying by the local press
today.
</P>
<P>
Almost 60 percent of the price of a packet of cigarattes is
collected as taxes, which represent 0.3 percent of the gross
domestic product of the country.
</P>
<P>
Cigarette sales in Venezuela have been diminishing slowly since
1994, said the director of the tobacco company, who dismissed an
immediate recovery of the sector in 1997. 
</P>
