<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
will leave Moscow's Central Clinical Hospital early next week, his
spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news briefing in the Kremlin, Yastrzhembsky
quoted the Kremlin doctors as saying that Yeltsin's health
condition is improving.
</P>
<P>
The president "will be released" from the hospital in the next
week, "after the coming weekend," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"With his recuperation going on at the current pace," Yeltsin
will be able to resume his traditional Monday meetings with the
presidential chief of staff, as well as consultations with the
Prime Minister that used to be held each Tuesday, Yastrzhembsky
said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin spent some three hours on Friday on paper work, with
about half of this time devoted to the drafting of an annual
message to the parliament, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian President has been hospitalized for pneumonia since
January 8. He underwent a heart bypass surgery on November 5 and
returned to the Kremlin on December 23. 
