<HEADLINE> Christopher Urges Israel to Talk with Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Outgoing Secretary of State
Warren Christopher on Friday urged Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu to try to resume peace talks with Syria.
</P>
<P>
In a farewell interview with international news agencies,
Christopher said Netanyahu's agreement with Yasser Arafat on
Israeli troops' pullback from the West Bank city of Hebron could
prompt an accord with Syria.
</P>
<P>
He praised Netanyahu as crossing "an important threshold",
stopping short of saying that Netanyahu had been converted to the
"land-for-peace" formula by handing most of Hebron to the
Palestinians under the Hebron deal.
</P>
