Israel and the rest of the Arab world," he said. And "by reaching
this agreement, by beginning redeployment... by committing to a
road map for the future, he will give... some encouragement to
those Arab countries that have wanted to see progress in peace."
</P>
<P>
He urged the Israeli prime minister to try to resume peace
talks with Syria as Syrian President Hafez Assad will soon be
"back in action" and ready to pursue more stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
"I would think that the Israeli government, if it gets an
opportunity, should test the willingness of the Syrians to get
into serious discussions," Christopher said. 
